RELEASE NOTES This is test case for GENSYMCID-1172 'Float-variable value limited ?'
BACKGROUND Overflow was observed when assigning a formula or value to float-variable in G2 2011 STD (observed in December release). Our goal was to write a regression test for that
SOLUTION We just implemented the test.
IMPLEMENTATION DETAILS We started with test kb attached to CID. But that kb was obviously defective. Result of TestRail test case might differ depending on if the operator is smart enough to press "post float" action in less then 1 second after pressing "conclude float" button, because of validity interval and formula present in the variable. After 1 second formula is recalculated and in fact what test operator sees is a value from random source - either freshly concluded one, or calculated from formula. They coincided in test kb, but this is only happened by chance. So we first of all modify validity-inteval to indefinite and default update interval to none.
TESTING Both tests fail in G2 2011 December release and pass at some point in HIP2016-08
NOTES Bug was observed in G2 Standard Edition while test suite is run in Enterprise Edition. So we are unlikely to ever detect the regression.
